The paper deals with algorithms for graph partitioning, specifically the balanced separator problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also involves spectral graph theory and matrix computations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.SD (Systems and Control), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
